            semester: 'fall 2023',
            review: "Overall, this is a decent course that reinforces and encourages the skill set of a good machine learning practitioner. TJ has done a lot to better the course, and it's definitely less nebulous than what I've seen in earlier reviews of the course.\nIf you want to make an A, start the projects early. Always get to the page limit of what's allowed for each of the assignments, but try your best to connect the results of your analysis back to problems, algorithms, or datasets you've chosen.\nThe grading really isn't as subjective as some other reviews may report. You will make a good grade (80+) on assignments if you're doing analysis versus figure summaries.\nIn spring of 2024, there was no midterm, but the final exam was very approachable so long as you watched every lecture. Every question seemed like reasonable distillations of the course material.\nPersonally, I think this course is a great representation of what is required to be a valuable researcher or ML engineer in an industry setting. Don't let anyone scare you; this class will force you to practice relevant techniques, and it's worth the time investment.",
