            review: "A very rewarding course. It is pretty fast paced - a lot of ML algorithms are covered and there is a lot of reading to do. However, you learn to use ML tools in the market (I had to program in Java and Python - many others used R) and to not reinvent the wheel. There are a couple of things I struggled with\n\nPicking the right datasets. You have to use the same dataset in 3 assignments, so ensure that you pick datasets\n\n\nrunning a bunch of classifiers on them to ensure that they don't all predict in the same or similar range, nor are they too easy (>95% accuracy) or too difficult (<50% accuracy)\nensuring you understand the underlying data - you'll have to really care about the data else you'll have a hard time explaining your results\n\n\nSwitching from Java to Python and back\n\nI'd recommend sticking with the following libraries/packages for the various assignments\n\nWeka for Assignment 1 (many also used Python and R)\nABAGAIL for Assignment 2 (This has a lot of starter code to help you)\nScikit Learn for Assignment 3 (Weka has ICA missing)\nBURLAP for Assignment 4\n",
